Crafting visually appealing summary widget for assignment
Crafting visually appealing summary widget for assignment


Solid work across the whole project — 11 idioms is a genuinely ambitious scope for one assignment. A few things that stand out as particularly well-executed:

The year slider linking two views (choropleth colours + area chart red dot + event popup) is the kind of cross-view coordination that separates a good dashboard from a great one. Most students just put independent charts side by side.

The Vega vs Vega-Lite split was a smart call — the treemap and waterfall chart have layout semantics that Vega-Lite's declarative grammar doesn't handle cleanly, and using raw Vega for those two while keeping everything else in Vega-Lite kept the codebase from getting messy.

Using no bind on the choropleth and wiring the controls through JS signals rather than Vega's built-in binding is also the right pattern for a page where you want a shared control bar above multiple views — Vega's native bind puts the control inside the chart container, which breaks unified layout.

Is there anything specific you want to revisit or improve now that it's submitted? Happy to help with a postmortem, refactoring ideas, or anything you want to carry forward into future projects.

