Scrutinized visualization spec for missing interactivity parameters
Scrutinized visualization spec for missing interactivity parameters
Got it. Here's a thorough read of the spec — the good parts and the real problems.

What's working
The layer structure is correct — geoshape underneath, text labels on top. The threshold color scale (
#FDDBC7 → 
#67001F) is a sensible sequential red ramp for risk. "width": "container" is the right call for a responsive layout. Tooltip fields are well chosen.

Problems
1. No params at all — the year slider can't work

This is the critical one. The project notes say the choropleth is controlled by an HTML year slider via areaView.signal(), but there is no params block in this spec. There's nothing for JS to push a signal into. A Vega-Lite view only accepts external signal updates if a named param exists first:

json
"params": [
  { "name": "year_select", "value": 2019 },
  { "name": "state_select", "value": null }
]
Without that, any view.signal('year_select', 2020) call in vega_lite_vis.js silently does nothing.

2. Wrong data file — the year filter has nothing to filter on

The data source is bushfire_risk_by_state.csv, but you have a separate bushfire_risk_by_state_multiyear.csv in the repo. The single-year file has no year column, so even if you added the param above, there'd be no transform filter to act on it. It needs to be:

json
"data": { "url": "bushfire_risk_by_state_multiyear.csv" }
…with a filter transform:

json
{ "filter": "datum.year == year_select" }
3. State label coordinates depend on GeoJSON properties that may not exist

json
"longitude": { "field": "properties.longitude" },
"latitude":  { "field": "properties.latitude" }
These fields need to be explicitly present in each feature's properties object in australia_states.geojson. If they're not there (centroid coordinates are not part of standard GeoJSON), the labels will render at (0°, 0°) — off the coast of Africa. The safer approach is to use the geoCentroid transform, or hardcode a label layer with a separate inline data source.

4. state_select filtering is also missing

If the HTML dropdown is supposed to highlight or isolate a state, there's no param or conditional encoding for it in this spec.

Minimal fix to wire up the year slider
json
{
  "$schema": "https://vega.github.io/schema/vega-lite/v5.json",
  "width": "container",
  "height": 320,
  "params": [
    { "name": "year_select", "value": 2019 }
  ],
  "projection": { "type": "mercator", "center": [134, -28], "scale": 550 },
  "layer": [
    {
      "data": { "url": "bushfire_risk_by_state_multiyear.csv" },
      "transform": [
        { "filter": "datum.year == year_select" },
        {
          "lookup": "state_code",
          "from": {
            "data": { "url": "australia_states.geojson", "format": { "type": "geojson" } },
            "key": "properties.state_code",
            "fields": ["type", "geometry", "properties"]
          }
        },
        { "calculate": "datum.fire_risk_score / 100", "as": "risk_normalised" }
      ],
      "mark": { "type": "geoshape", "stroke": "#fff", "strokeWidth": 1 },
      "encoding": {
        "shape": { "field": "geometry", "type": "geojson" },
        "color": { ... }
      }
    }
  ]
}
Note the lookup direction is flipped from what you have — join CSV rows to GeoJSON shapes (not GeoJSON to CSV), because Vega-Lite's geoshape mark needs the geometry on the primary data row.

