Spec fix — the root cause of all three errors

The lookup's from block had "format": {"type": "geojson"}. Vega only understands geojson as a format for primary data (it triggers the feature-extraction pipeline). For a lookup source it must be:

json
"format": { "type": "json", "property": "features" }
"property": "features" tells Vega to unwrap the FeatureCollection and treat each feature as a row, so properties.state_code and geometry resolve correctly. That fixes errors 1 and 2; error 3 (Infinite extent for year) will need the same diagnosis applied to your area/dual-axis CSV column names.

Click interaction — how it works

choroplethView.addEventListener('click', fn) fires with item.datum containing the clicked row. The handler:

Clicking a state → pushes state_select signal into the map (dims others, white stroke on selected), syncs the dropdown, calls updateStateBox(code)
Clicking the same state again → deselects everything, resets to the default 4-card view
Clicking blank ocean → same deselect behaviour
The state info box shows a different set of 4 KPI cards per state: risk score, % fire-prone land, risk change since 2001, and the state's worst event with deaths + homes below.

