Same two errors we've fixed before on the choropleth — geojson format type not valid for lookup sources, and the geometry lookup failing downstream. Fix is identical: change "type": "json", "property": "features" in every lookup's from block.


Ran a command, read a file
Ran a command, read a file
Two fixes applied to all four panels:

"format": {"type": "geojson"} → "format": {"type": "json", "property": "features"} — this is the root cause of the Unknown data format type: geojson error. When GeoJSON is used as a lookup source (not primary data), Vega doesn't support the geojson format type. Using json with property: features unwraps the FeatureCollection so each feature becomes a row with properties.state_code and geometry accessible.
Added "shape": {"field": "geometry", "type": "geojson"} encoding to each panel — required when geometry comes from a lookup field rather than being parsed automatically as primary data.
The 404 error is for the slope_chart.vg.json file which no longer exists in the repo since we replaced it. You can safely delete that file from the repo, or just ignore the 404 since the embed call has been removed from vega_lite_vis.js.







